<div id="review_544310769" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/544310769" />
    <a title="Narges Moini" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4275523-narges-moini"><img alt="Narges Moini" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1509724014p2/4275523.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/544310769?book_show_action=true">Feb 23, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Narges Moini" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Narges Moini" href="/user/show/4275523-narges-moini">Narges Moini</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780571224449" href="/book/show/945817.The_Melancholy_Death_of_Oyster_Boy_Other_Stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4275523-narges-moini?shelf=%D8%B2%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D8%B5%D9%84%DB%8C">زبان-اصلی</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer544310769" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6109616256728619402"><b> The girl who turned into a bed! </b><br/><br/>It happened that day<br/>she picked up a strange pussy willow.<br/>Her head swelled up white<br/>and a soft as a pillow.<br/><br/>Her skin, which had turned<br/>all flaky and rotten,<br/>was now replaced<br/>with 100% cotton.<br/><br/>Through her organs and torso<br/>she sprouted like wings,<br/>a beautiful set<br/>of mattress and springs.<br/><br/><br/><br/>It was so terribly strange<br/>that I started to weep.<br/>But at least after that<br/>I had a nice place to sleep</span>

          </span>
        </div>


